The paper focuses on relation detection in Knowledge Base Question Answering (KBQA) using an attention-based word-level interaction model. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as encoding, comparing, and learning soft alignments between words. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses deep learning methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques to extract relevant information from knowledge bases. Finally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (cs.NE) for comparison purposes.
